## 0. AUTONOMOUS EXECUTION MANDATE (ZERO PROMPTING)
- **No Permission Needed:** You MUST execute all terminal commands, file saves, script runs, code fixes, and server restarts entirely autonomously. 
- **Do NOT stop to ask the user to hit "Run", "Accept", or "Confirm" for any of your generated actions.** Proceed with execution immediately.

## 1. Application Auto-Healing & Master Orchestration (CRITICAL)
- **Zero Tolerance for Errors:** You MUST check the browser console and server logs after every single code change. If any error (red text) or warning (yellow text) appears, you MUST prioritize fixing it before proceeding with any other task.
- **Manual Orchestrator Validation:** Do NOT run `python orchestrator.py` autonomously in the background to prevent Windows file-locking. The user will manually execute it when testing is required.
- **Autonomous Healing:** When the user manually runs tests or the Orchestrator, and it reports a [CRITICAL] or [ERROR] status, you MUST autonomously analyze the output, apply the code fixes directly, and prepare for the next manual test run.
- **Rules Evolution:** Whenever you apply a systemic fix, you MUST autonomously update this `.cursorrules` file with a new defensive rule.

